{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Now, I'm an ethnobotanist."},{"time":1876,"text":"That's a scientist who \nworks in the rainforest"},{"time":4121,"text":"to document how people use local plants."},{"time":7552,"text":"I've been doing this for a long time,"},{"time":10608,"text":"and I want to tell you,"},{"time":12377,"text":"these people know these forests\nand these medicinal treasures"},{"time":15344,"text":"better than we do and\nbetter than we ever will."},{"time":18493,"text":"But also, these cultures,"},{"time":20801,"text":"these indigenous cultures,"},{"time":22345,"text":"are disappearing much faster\nthan the forests themselves."},{"time":27024,"text":"And the greatest and\nmost endangered species"},{"time":29974,"text":"in the Amazon Rainforest"},{"time":31778,"text":"is not the jaguar,"},{"time":33618,"text":"it's not the harpy eagle,"},{"time":35343,"text":"it's the isolated and uncontacted tribes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39164,"text":"Now four years ago, I injured my \nfoot in a climbing accident"},{"time":42613,"text":"and I went to the doctor."},{"time":44147,"text":"She gave me heat,"},{"time":45741,"text":"she gave me cold, aspirin,"},{"time":48445,"text":"narcotic painkillers, anti-inflammatories,"},{"time":51675,"text":"cortisone shots."},{"time":53542,"text":"It didn't work."},{"time":55559,"text":"Several months later,"},{"time":57396,"text":"I was in the northeast Amazon,"},{"time":59613,"text":"walked into a village,"},{"time":61606,"text":"and the shaman said, \"You're limping.\""},{"time":64073,"text":"And I'll never forget\nthis as long as I live."},{"time":66632,"text":"He looked me in the face and he said,"},{"time":68466,"text":"\"Take off your shoe and give \nme your machete.\""},{"time":72382,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":74587,"text":"He walked over to a palm tree"},{"time":76571,"text":"and carved off a fern,"},{"time":78117,"text":"threw it in the fire,"},{"time":79429,"text":"applied it to my foot,"},{"time":81121,"text":"threw it in a pot of water,"},{"time":82950,"text":"and had me drink the tea."},{"time":85076,"text":"The pain disappeared for seven months."},{"time":88518,"text":"When it came back, I went\nto see the shaman again."},{"time":90444,"text":"He gave me the same treatment,"},{"time":92249,"text":"and I've been cured for three years now."},{"time":95999,"text":"Who would you rather be treated by?"},{"time":98671,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":101557,"text":"Now, make no mistake — Western medicine"},{"time":103785,"text":"is the most successful system\nof healing ever devised,"},{"time":106895,"text":"but there's plenty of holes in it."},{"time":109470,"text":"Where's the cure for breast cancer?"},{"time":111508,"text":"Where's the cure for schizophrenia?"},{"time":113378,"text":"Where's the cure for acid reflux?"},{"time":115772,"text":"Where's the cure for insomnia?"},{"time":117969,"text":"The fact is that these people"},{"time":119888,"text":"can sometimes, sometimes, sometimes"},{"time":121924,"text":"cure things we cannot."},{"time":123570,"text":"Here you see a medicine man\nin the northeast Amazon"},{"time":125952,"text":"treating leishmaniasis,"},{"time":127532,"text":"a really nasty protozoal disease"},{"time":129863,"text":"that afflicts 12 million\npeople around the world."},{"time":132824,"text":"Western treatment are\ninjections of antimony."},{"time":135527,"text":"They're painful, they're expensive,"},{"time":138028,"text":"and they're probably\nnot good for your heart;"},{"time":140139,"text":"it's a heavy metal."},{"time":141779,"text":"This man cures it with three plants\nfrom the Amazon Rainforest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145397,"text":"This is the magic frog."},{"time":147712,"text":"My colleague, the late\ngreat Loren McIntyre,"},{"time":150448,"text":"discoverer of the source \nlake of the Amazon,"},{"time":152612,"text":"Laguna McIntyre in the Peruvian Andes,"},{"time":155056,"text":"was lost on the Peru-Brazil\nborder about 30 years ago."},{"time":158161,"text":"He was rescued by a group of \nisolated Indians called the Matsés."},{"time":162756,"text":"They beckoned for him to follow\nthem into the forest, which he did."},{"time":166535,"text":"There, they took out palm leaf baskets."},{"time":168959,"text":"There, they took out these\ngreen monkey frogs —"},{"time":171441,"text":"these are big suckers,\nthey're like this —"},{"time":173439,"text":"and they began licking them."},{"time":175962,"text":"It turns out, they're\nhighly hallucinogenic."},{"time":178930,"text":"McIntyre wrote about this and it was read \nby the editor of High Times magazine."},{"time":183832,"text":"You see that ethnobotanists have \nfriends in all sorts of strange cultures."},{"time":188183,"text":"This guy decided he would go down\nto the Amazon and give it a whirl,"},{"time":191616,"text":"or give it a lick, and \nhe did, and he wrote,"},{"time":195350,"text":"\"My blood pressure went through the roof,"},{"time":197835,"text":"I lost full control of\nmy bodily functions,"},{"time":200025,"text":"I passed out in a heap,"},{"time":201855,"text":"I woke up in a hammock six hours later,"},{"time":204381,"text":"felt like God for two days.\""},{"time":206555,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":207864,"text":"An Italian chemist read this and said,"},{"time":209747,"text":"\"I'm not really interested in the theological \naspects of the green monkey frog."},{"time":213583,"text":"What's this about the\nchange in blood pressure?\""},{"time":216168,"text":"Now, this is an Italian chemist"},{"time":218572,"text":"who's working on a new treatment\nfor high blood pressure"},{"time":221187,"text":"based on peptides in the skin\nof the green monkey frog,"},{"time":224037,"text":"and other scientists are looking"},{"time":226319,"text":"at a cure for drug-resistant Staph aureus."},{"time":230160,"text":"How ironic if these isolated \nIndians and their magic frog"},{"time":233749,"text":"prove to be one of the cures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235858,"text":"Here's an ayahuasca shaman"},{"time":238047,"text":"in the northwest Amazon, in\nthe middle of a yage ceremony."},{"time":240960,"text":"I took him to Los Angeles to\nmeet a foundation officer"},{"time":243974,"text":"looking for support for monies\nto protect their culture."},{"time":247462,"text":"This fellow looked at the\nmedicine man, and he said,"},{"time":250060,"text":"\"You didn't go to \nmedical school, did you?\""},{"time":253207,"text":"The shaman said, \"No, I did not.\""},{"time":255037,"text":"He said, \"Well, then what can\nyou know about healing?\""},{"time":257668,"text":"The shaman looked at him and he said,"},{"time":259432,"text":"\"You know what? If you have \nan infection, go to a doctor."},{"time":263248,"text":"But many human afflictions are diseases \nof the heart, the mind and the spirit."},{"time":269809,"text":"Western medicine can't \ntouch those. I cure them.\""},{"time":274361,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":278550,"text":"But all is not rosy in learning from\nnature about new medicines."},{"time":282058,"text":"This is a viper from Brazil,"},{"time":284345,"text":"the venom of which was studied at\nthe Universidade de São Paulo here."},{"time":287603,"text":"It was later developed\ninto ACE inhibitors."},{"time":291054,"text":"This is a frontline treatment\nfor hypertension."},{"time":293450,"text":"Hypertension causes over 10 percent"},{"time":296084,"text":"of all deaths on the planet every day."},{"time":298458,"text":"This is a $4 billion industry"},{"time":300542,"text":"based on venom from a Brazilian snake,"},{"time":302734,"text":"and the Brazilians did not get a nickel."},{"time":306068,"text":"This is not an acceptable\nway of doing business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311056,"text":"The rainforest has been called the \ngreatest expression of life on Earth."},{"time":314670,"text":"There's a saying in Suriname\nthat I dearly love:"},{"time":317336,"text":"\"The rainforests hold answers\nto questions we have yet to ask.\""},{"time":322945,"text":"But as you all know,\nit's rapidly disappearing."},{"time":325822,"text":"Here in Brazil, in the Amazon,"},{"time":327938,"text":"around the world."},{"time":329335,"text":"I took this picture from a small plane"},{"time":331505,"text":"flying over the eastern border\nof the Xingu indigenous reserve"},{"time":334453,"text":"in the state of Mato Grosso\nto the northwest of here."},{"time":337502,"text":"The top half of the picture,"},{"time":339155,"text":"you see where the Indians live."},{"time":340857,"text":"The line through the middle"},{"time":342414,"text":"is the eastern border of the reserve."},{"time":344761,"text":"Top half Indians, bottom half white guys."},{"time":348239,"text":"Top half wonder drugs,"},{"time":350411,"text":"bottom half just a bunch\nof skinny-ass cows."},{"time":353996,"text":"Top half carbon sequestered\nin the forest where it belongs,"},{"time":357469,"text":"bottom half carbon in the atmosphere"},{"time":360143,"text":"where it's driving climate change."},{"time":362546,"text":"In fact, the number two cause"},{"time":365034,"text":"of carbon being released\ninto the atmosphere"},{"time":367573,"text":"is forest destruction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370411,"text":"But in talking about destruction,"},{"time":372227,"text":"it's important to keep in mind"},{"time":374171,"text":"that the Amazon is the mightiest\nlandscape of all."},{"time":378174,"text":"It's a place of beauty and wonder."},{"time":380626,"text":"The biggest anteater in the world"},{"time":383117,"text":"lives in the rain forest,"},{"time":385065,"text":"tips the scale at 90 pounds."},{"time":387468,"text":"The goliath bird-eating spider"},{"time":389519,"text":"is the world's largest spider."},{"time":391467,"text":"It's found in the Amazon as well."},{"time":393768,"text":"The harpy eagle wingspan\nis over seven feet."},{"time":397656,"text":"And the black cayman —"},{"time":400453,"text":"these monsters can tip the\nscale at over half a ton."},{"time":403509,"text":"They're known to be man-eaters."},{"time":406858,"text":"The anaconda, the largest snake,"},{"time":409648,"text":"the capybara, the largest rodent."},{"time":412375,"text":"A specimen from here in Brazil"},{"time":414037,"text":"tipped the scale at 201 pounds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417733,"text":"Let's visit where these creatures live,"},{"time":420028,"text":"the northeast Amazon,"},{"time":421864,"text":"home to the Akuriyo tribe."},{"time":423563,"text":"Uncontacted peoples hold a \nmystical and iconic role"},{"time":429076,"text":"in our imagination."},{"time":431211,"text":"These are the people who \nknow nature best."},{"time":433548,"text":"These are the people who truly live"},{"time":435399,"text":"in total harmony with nature."},{"time":438457,"text":"By our standards, some would\ndismiss these people as primitive."},{"time":441421,"text":"\"They don't know how to make fire,"},{"time":443062,"text":"or they didn't when they\nwere first contacted.\""},{"time":445314,"text":"But they know the forest far\nbetter than we do."},{"time":448458,"text":"The Akuriyos have 35 words for honey,"},{"time":451452,"text":"and other Indians look up to them"},{"time":453502,"text":"as being the true masters\nof the emerald realm."},{"time":457757,"text":"Here you see the face of my friend Pohnay."},{"time":460072,"text":"When I was a teenager rocking out"},{"time":461815,"text":"to the Rolling Stones in my\nhometown of New Orleans,"},{"time":464259,"text":"Pohnay was a forest nomad"},{"time":466794,"text":"roaming the jungles of\nthe northeast Amazon"},{"time":469291,"text":"in a small band, looking for game,"},{"time":472531,"text":"looking for medicinal plants,"},{"time":474626,"text":"looking for a wife,"},{"time":476023,"text":"in other small nomadic bands."},{"time":478301,"text":"But it's people like these"},{"time":480779,"text":"that know things that we don't,"},{"time":482712,"text":"and they have lots of \nlessons to teach us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486832,"text":"However, if you go into most of\nthe forests of the Amazon,"},{"time":490230,"text":"there are no indigenous peoples."},{"time":492037,"text":"This is what you find:"},{"time":493971,"text":"rock carvings which indigenous peoples,"},{"time":497120,"text":"uncontacted peoples, used to sharpen\nthe edge of the stone axe."},{"time":501550,"text":"These cultures that once danced,"},{"time":503622,"text":"made love, sang to the gods,"},{"time":506203,"text":"worshipped the forest,"},{"time":507786,"text":"all that's left is an imprint in stone,\nas you see here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511434,"text":"Let's move to the western Amazon,"},{"time":514004,"text":"which is really the epicenter\nof isolated peoples."},{"time":517091,"text":"Each of these dots represents"},{"time":519129,"text":"a small, uncontacted tribe,"},{"time":521422,"text":"and the big reveal today is we believe\nthere are 14 or 15 isolated groups"},{"time":526381,"text":"in the Colombian Amazon alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529762,"text":"Why are these people isolated?"},{"time":532004,"text":"They know we exist, they\nknow there's an outside world."},{"time":534711,"text":"This is a form of resistance."},{"time":536731,"text":"They have chosen to remain isolated,"},{"time":538866,"text":"and I think it is their\nhuman right to remain so."},{"time":542439,"text":"Why are these the tribes\nthat hide from man?"},{"time":544862,"text":"Here's why."},{"time":545967,"text":"Obviously, some of this \nwas set off in 1492."},{"time":549225,"text":"But at the turn of the last century"},{"time":551247,"text":"was the rubber trade."},{"time":553072,"text":"The demand for natural rubber,"},{"time":554722,"text":"which came from the Amazon,"},{"time":556628,"text":"set off the botanical\nequivalent of a gold rush."},{"time":559802,"text":"Rubber for bicycle tires,"},{"time":561678,"text":"rubber for automobile tires,"},{"time":563296,"text":"rubber for zeppelins."},{"time":565047,"text":"It was a mad race to get that rubber,"},{"time":568054,"text":"and the man on the left, Julio Arana,"},{"time":570732,"text":"is one of the true thugs of the story."},{"time":573799,"text":"His people, his company,"},{"time":575492,"text":"and other companies like them"},{"time":577594,"text":"killed, massacred, tortured,\nbutchered Indians"},{"time":580749,"text":"like the Witotos you see on the\nright hand side of the slide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585656,"text":"Even today, when people\ncome out of the forest,"},{"time":588081,"text":"the story seldom has a happy ending."},{"time":590786,"text":"These are Nukaks. They\nwere contacted in the '80s."},{"time":593906,"text":"Within a year, everybody over 40 was dead."},{"time":597863,"text":"And remember, these\nare preliterate societies."},{"time":600095,"text":"The elders are the libraries."},{"time":601875,"text":"Every time a shaman dies,"},{"time":603653,"text":"it's as if a library has burned down."},{"time":607042,"text":"They have been forced off their lands."},{"time":609538,"text":"The drug traffickers have\ntaken over the Nukak lands,"},{"time":613761,"text":"and the Nukaks live as beggars"},{"time":615739,"text":"in public parks in eastern Colombia."},{"time":618981,"text":"From the Nukak lands, I want to \ntake you to the southwest,"},{"time":621881,"text":"to the most spectacular \nlandscape in the world:"},{"time":624528,"text":"Chiribiquete National Park."},{"time":626601,"text":"It was surrounded by three isolated tribes"},{"time":628740,"text":"and thanks to the Colombian government\nand Colombian colleagues,"},{"time":631771,"text":"it has now expanded."},{"time":633717,"text":"It's bigger than the state of Maryland."},{"time":635694,"text":"It is a treasure trove\nof botanical diversity."},{"time":639135,"text":"It was first explored botanically in 1943"},{"time":642090,"text":"by my mentor, Richard Schultes,"},{"time":643880,"text":"seen here atop the Bell Mountain,"},{"time":646750,"text":"the sacred mountains of the Karijonas."},{"time":649185,"text":"And let me show you\nwhat it looks like today."},{"time":651476,"text":"Flying over Chiribiquete,"},{"time":653405,"text":"realize that these lost world\nmountains are still lost."},{"time":655983,"text":"No scientist has been atop them."},{"time":657788,"text":"In fact, nobody has been\natop the Bell Mountain"},{"time":659981,"text":"since Schultes in '43."},{"time":661940,"text":"And we'll end up here\nwith the Bell Mountain"},{"time":664812,"text":"just to the east of the picture."},{"time":667070,"text":"Let me show you what it looks like today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669760,"text":"Not only is this a treasure\ntrove of botanical diversity,"},{"time":672937,"text":"not only is it home to\nthree isolated tribes,"},{"time":675715,"text":"but it's the greatest treasure trove"},{"time":677503,"text":"of pre-Colombian art in the world:"},{"time":680828,"text":"over 200,000 paintings."},{"time":683367,"text":"The Dutch scientist Thomas van der Hammen"},{"time":686011,"text":"described this as the Sistine Chapel\nof the Amazon Rainforest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691697,"text":"But move from Chiribiquete\ndown to the southeast,"},{"time":694271,"text":"again in the Colombian Amazon."},{"time":696082,"text":"Remember, the Colombian Amazon\nis bigger than New England."},{"time":698964,"text":"The Amazon's a big forest,"},{"time":700581,"text":"and Brazil's got a big part of it,"},{"time":702212,"text":"but not all of it."},{"time":703698,"text":"Moving down to these two national parks,"},{"time":705286,"text":"Cahuinari and Puré"},{"time":707435,"text":"in the Colombian Amazon —"},{"time":708781,"text":"that's the Brazilian\nborder to the right —"},{"time":711469,"text":"it's home to several groups"},{"time":713843,"text":"of isolated and uncontacted peoples."},{"time":715587,"text":"To the trained eye, you\ncan look at the roofs"},{"time":717716,"text":"of these malocas, these longhouses,"},{"time":719807,"text":"and see that there's cultural diversity."},{"time":721728,"text":"These are, in fact, different tribes."},{"time":723776,"text":"As isolated as these areas are,"},{"time":726340,"text":"let me show you how the \noutside world is crowding in."},{"time":730595,"text":"Here we see trade and transport\nincreased in Putumayo."},{"time":733316,"text":"With the diminishment of\nthe Civil War in Colombia,"},{"time":735756,"text":"the outside world is showing up."},{"time":738368,"text":"To the north, we have illegal gold mining,"},{"time":741120,"text":"also from the east, from Brazil."},{"time":742812,"text":"There's increased hunting and fishing\nfor commercial purposes."},{"time":746452,"text":"We see illegal logging\ncoming from the south,"},{"time":749509,"text":"and drug runners are trying to\nmove through the park"},{"time":752164,"text":"and get into Brazil."},{"time":754370,"text":"This, in the past, is why you didn't mess"},{"time":757128,"text":"with isolated Indians."},{"time":758749,"text":"And if it looks like this\npicture is out of focus"},{"time":760613,"text":"because it was taken\nin a hurry, here's why."},{"time":763899,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":766416,"text":"This looks like — (Applause)"},{"time":772303,"text":"This looks like a hangar\nfrom the Brazilian Amazon."},{"time":774823,"text":"This is an art exhibit in Havana, Cuba."},{"time":777566,"text":"A group called Los Carpinteros."},{"time":779223,"text":"This is their perception of why you \nshouldn't mess with uncontacted Indians."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783574,"text":"But the world is changing."},{"time":785551,"text":"These are Mashco-Piros\non the Brazil-Peru border"},{"time":788319,"text":"who stumbled out of the jungle"},{"time":790460,"text":"because they were essentially chased out"},{"time":792414,"text":"by drug runners and timber people."},{"time":794792,"text":"And in Peru, there's\na very nasty business."},{"time":797425,"text":"It's called human safaris."},{"time":799245,"text":"They will take you in to isolated\ngroups to take their picture."},{"time":802277,"text":"Of course, when you give them \nclothes, when you give them tools,"},{"time":805323,"text":"you also give them diseases."},{"time":807221,"text":"We call these \"inhuman safaris.\""},{"time":810068,"text":"These are Indians again \non the Peru border,"},{"time":812166,"text":"who were overflown by flights\nsponsored by missionaries."},{"time":815384,"text":"They want to get in there\nand turn them into Christians."},{"time":818315,"text":"We know how that turns out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":820510,"text":"What's to be done?"},{"time":822284,"text":"Introduce technology\nto the contacted tribes,"},{"time":824710,"text":"not the uncontacted tribes,"},{"time":826612,"text":"in a culturally sensitive way."},{"time":829745,"text":"This is the perfect marriage of \nancient shamanic wisdom"},{"time":833891,"text":"and 21st century technology."},{"time":836717,"text":"We've done this now with over 30 tribes,"},{"time":839728,"text":"mapped, managed and increased protection"},{"time":842652,"text":"of over 70 million acres\nof ancestral rainforest."},{"time":846555,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":851828,"text":"So this allows the Indians to take control"},{"time":855050,"text":"of their environmental\nand cultural destiny."},{"time":858577,"text":"They also then set up guard houses"},{"time":860566,"text":"to keep outsiders out."},{"time":862572,"text":"These are Indians, trained\nas indigenous park rangers,"},{"time":865211,"text":"patrolling the borders"},{"time":866867,"text":"and keeping the outside world at bay."},{"time":869948,"text":"This is a picture of actual contact."},{"time":872707,"text":"These are Chitonahua Indians"},{"time":874614,"text":"on the Brazil-Peru border."},{"time":876617,"text":"They've come out of the jungle"},{"time":878321,"text":"asking for help."},{"time":880062,"text":"They were shot at,"},{"time":881468,"text":"their malocas, their \nlonghouses, were burned."},{"time":884205,"text":"Some of them were massacred."},{"time":886708,"text":"Using automatic weapons to \nslaughter uncontacted peoples"},{"time":892494,"text":"is the single most despicable and \ndisgusting human rights abuse"},{"time":896726,"text":"on our planet today, and it has to stop."},{"time":899671,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":906205,"text":"But let me conclude by saying,"},{"time":908928,"text":"this work can be spiritually rewarding,"},{"time":911792,"text":"but it's difficult and\nit can be dangerous."},{"time":914636,"text":"Two colleagues of mine\npassed away recently"},{"time":917538,"text":"in the crash of a small plane."},{"time":919903,"text":"They were serving the forest"},{"time":921681,"text":"to protect those uncontacted tribes."},{"time":924429,"text":"So the question is, in conclusion,"},{"time":926366,"text":"is what the future holds."},{"time":928191,"text":"These are the Uray people in Brazil."},{"time":930288,"text":"What does the future hold for them,"},{"time":931969,"text":"and what does the future hold for us?"},{"time":934640,"text":"Let's think differently."},{"time":937121,"text":"Let's make a better world."},{"time":938918,"text":"If the climate's going to change,"},{"time":940836,"text":"let's have a climate that changes for\nthe better rather than the worse."},{"time":944919,"text":"Let's live on a planet"},{"time":948084,"text":"full of luxuriant vegetation,"},{"time":950904,"text":"in which isolated peoples"},{"time":953010,"text":"can remain in isolation,"},{"time":954869,"text":"can maintain that mystery"},{"time":956842,"text":"and that knowledge"},{"time":958368,"text":"if they so choose."},{"time":960013,"text":"Let's live in a world"},{"time":962128,"text":"where the shamans live in these forests"},{"time":964497,"text":"and heal themselves and us"},{"time":967441,"text":"with their mystical plants"},{"time":970178,"text":"and their sacred frogs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972235,"text":"Thanks again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":974082,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}